1
00:00:42,014 --> 00:00:44,050
[ Narrator ]
The future:

2
00:00:44,134 --> 00:00:46,409
The polar ice caps
have melted,

3
00:00:46,494 --> 00:00:49,088
covering the Earth
with water.

4
00:00:49,174 --> 00:00:53,406
Those who survived
have adapted...

5
00:00:53,454 --> 00:00:55,331
to a new world.

6
00:02:20,614 --> 00:02:23,208
[ Gargling ]

7
00:02:31,774 --> 00:02:33,605
[ Metal Clangs ]

8
00:04:56,134 --> 00:04:58,011
[ Whistles ]

9
00:05:13,134 --> 00:05:16,331
Bad luck, English.

10
00:05:16,374 --> 00:05:20,765
But the Slavers are producing
a good grade of poxy these days.

11
00:05:20,814 --> 00:05:23,567
Cost you a handful of dirt--
or maybe that wind chime.

12
00:05:23,654 --> 00:05:27,249
- What are you doin' here?
- Just waiting.

13
00:05:27,334 --> 00:05:30,246
Take your hand
off the sail.

14
00:05:30,294 --> 00:05:32,649
Take it off!

15
00:05:32,734 --> 00:05:36,443
l've seen your boat before.
Haven't seen you.

16
00:05:37,454 --> 00:05:40,093
Took it legal.

17
00:05:40,174 --> 00:05:42,927
Previous owner was dead on the tiller
when l found it.

18
00:05:43,014 --> 00:05:45,812
You had another hour
before l traded up again.

19
00:05:45,894 --> 00:05:48,362
[ Laughing ]
Just improving my means.

20
00:05:49,814 --> 00:05:52,044
- Well, l owe you then.
- No, thanks.

21
00:05:52,134 --> 00:05:57,128
l got all the supplies l need.
Just came from an atoll.

22
00:05:57,174 --> 00:06:00,052
Eight days east,
if you're interested.

23
00:06:02,134 --> 00:06:05,649
- Two drifters meet,
something needs to be exchanged.
- l know the code.

24
00:06:05,734 --> 00:06:08,248
But l'll give you this one
for free.

25
00:06:09,774 --> 00:06:11,605
Nothing's free
in Waterworld.

26
00:06:11,694 --> 00:06:13,207
Ha-ha. Yeah.

27
00:06:24,054 --> 00:06:26,249
Smokers.

28
00:06:26,294 --> 00:06:28,250
Just enough wind
to get away clean.

29
00:06:32,014 --> 00:06:33,925
[ Drifter ]
Forget the bag.

30
00:06:37,774 --> 00:06:41,449
lt's not worth it. You'll never
make it with your sails down.

31
00:06:41,534 --> 00:06:43,923
Hey!
[ Laughing ]

32
00:06:44,014 --> 00:06:45,891
[ Gobbling Sound,
Laughing ]

33
00:06:55,334 --> 00:06:57,450
What can l say?
[ Laughing ]

34
00:07:16,774 --> 00:07:19,971
- Joe, he's goin' for it.
- What the hell?

35
00:07:24,814 --> 00:07:26,770
Never seen that before.

36
00:07:30,414 --> 00:07:32,609
Here we go! Go!
Drive! Drive!

37
00:07:37,534 --> 00:07:40,367
Faster! Faster! Whoo!

38
00:08:00,374 --> 00:08:02,569
Come on! He's gonna get it!
He's gonna get it!

39
00:08:21,454 --> 00:08:23,604
- Pick her up!
- Get it! Get it!

40
00:08:23,694 --> 00:08:25,605
[ lndistinct Shout ]

41
00:08:43,334 --> 00:08:45,165
[ Curses ln Hindi ]

42
00:08:51,374 --> 00:08:53,842
0h, no!

43
00:09:00,454 --> 00:09:03,810
[ Shouting, Gunfire ]

44
00:09:04,814 --> 00:09:08,170
[ Screaming ]

45
00:09:38,254 --> 00:09:41,007
lnbound!
Straight out from the gates.

46
00:09:50,094 --> 00:09:51,971
English.

47
00:09:54,534 --> 00:09:58,413
Flag's down, drifter.
We got enough traders.

48
00:10:04,334 --> 00:10:07,167
[ Murmuring ]

49
00:10:11,534 --> 00:10:14,094
Dirt.

50
00:10:14,134 --> 00:10:16,011
0pen the gates!

51
00:10:53,574 --> 00:10:56,134
[ Man Coughing,
People Chattering ]

52
00:10:56,174 --> 00:10:58,893
[ Man ]
Bones to berries.

53
00:10:58,974 --> 00:11:00,965
Veins to vine.

54
00:11:01,054 --> 00:11:05,093
These tendons to trees.
This blood to brine.

55
00:11:05,134 --> 00:11:06,726
Too old she was.

56
00:11:06,814 --> 00:11:11,205
This woman does leave us,
recycled and enshrined...

57
00:11:11,254 --> 00:11:14,007
in the presence
of Him who leads us.

58
00:11:22,214 --> 00:11:25,365
[ Boys Chattering ]

59
00:11:31,374 --> 00:11:35,686
- [ Boys Complaining ]
- What is that?

60
00:11:40,014 --> 00:11:42,289
You know me?

61
00:11:42,374 --> 00:11:44,205
l know what you are.

62
00:11:44,294 --> 00:11:47,923
Good. Then you know if you
look for trouble while you're here,

63
00:11:48,014 --> 00:11:49,970
you'll find more
than you can handle.

64
00:11:51,214 --> 00:11:53,682
You got two hours.

65
00:11:56,174 --> 00:11:58,051
l'll only need one.

66
00:12:07,774 --> 00:12:10,208
[ Boy ]
He's comin' over here.

67
00:12:15,414 --> 00:12:17,291
- Me.
- You each get one...

68
00:12:17,334 --> 00:12:19,768
if everything's here
when l get back.

69
00:12:28,214 --> 00:12:30,011
- Pure dirt.
- [ People Murmuring ]

70
00:12:30,094 --> 00:12:32,369
3.2 kilos.

71
00:12:34,294 --> 00:12:37,366
How'd you come by
so much of it?

72
00:12:37,454 --> 00:12:40,093
Another atoll
30 horizons west of here.

73
00:12:40,174 --> 00:12:42,210
Where'd they get it?

74
00:12:42,254 --> 00:12:45,371
- They didn't say.
- [ Man ] We heard about that place--

75
00:12:45,454 --> 00:12:47,888
that they was all killed.

76
00:12:49,614 --> 00:12:51,730
- That's why they didn't say.
- Smokers?

77
00:12:51,814 --> 00:12:54,886
Maybe Smokers,
maybe Slavers.

78
00:12:56,254 --> 00:12:58,973
So what's the word?
We tradin' or not?

79
00:12:59,054 --> 00:13:03,570
We'll tally it
like, uh, pure hydro.

80
00:13:07,014 --> 00:13:09,847
Works out to... 62 chits.

81
00:13:09,934 --> 00:13:12,607
[ Coins Clanging ]

82
00:13:12,654 --> 00:13:14,531
l want twice that.

83
00:13:14,574 --> 00:13:18,089
[ 0nlookers Murmuring ]

84
00:13:18,174 --> 00:13:22,087
- l just want one sip of hydro!
- No, not 'til you tell me.

85
00:13:22,134 --> 00:13:25,251
She got inkings on her back.
l seen her.

86
00:13:25,294 --> 00:13:28,366
They say if you read
the marks on the child,

87
00:13:28,454 --> 00:13:31,764
they'll lead ya
all the way to Dryland.

88
00:13:31,854 --> 00:13:34,812
- Dryland's a myth.
- Some still believe.

89
00:13:34,894 --> 00:13:37,852
They say the Smokers
even got an eye out for her.

90
00:13:39,494 --> 00:13:42,406
Well, then, we'd better
keep it to ourselves.

91
00:14:05,134 --> 00:14:07,932
- Help you?
- Yeah.

92
00:14:08,014 --> 00:14:10,164
- Where's the store?
- You found it.

93
00:14:15,694 --> 00:14:17,571
You don't have much.

94
00:14:18,734 --> 00:14:21,294
You the man
with the dirt?

95
00:14:38,094 --> 00:14:39,573
Skoal.

96
00:14:43,054 --> 00:14:45,522
- 0ne more.
- Make it two.

97
00:14:45,614 --> 00:14:49,209
A man this rich will buy
for a fellow outwater, l'm sure.

98
00:14:49,294 --> 00:14:51,524
0ne.

99
00:14:53,894 --> 00:14:57,569
That's an interesting
pair of boots you got.

100
00:14:57,614 --> 00:14:59,684
- Trade?
- No.

101
00:14:59,774 --> 00:15:01,765
Shame.

102
00:15:08,214 --> 00:15:11,047
Enola.
Hey, what are you doing?

103
00:15:11,134 --> 00:15:14,763
- No, you can't do that.
- l need another piece.
l want to draw some more.

104
00:15:14,854 --> 00:15:17,368
l'll get it to you.
Just stay in the back.

105
00:15:17,454 --> 00:15:20,446
With all those chits,
you could order up a bath.

106
00:15:20,494 --> 00:15:23,054
- Have you ever had a freshwater bath?
- Why are you talkin' to me?

107
00:15:23,094 --> 00:15:24,971
Just being friendly.

108
00:15:30,014 --> 00:15:32,244
- ls that a tomato plant?
- Yeah.

109
00:15:32,334 --> 00:15:34,404
You have a keen eye.

110
00:15:34,494 --> 00:15:36,485
Saw one in a picture.
How much?

111
00:15:42,454 --> 00:15:44,331
Half your chits.

112
00:15:55,374 --> 00:15:58,366
- l'll take them too.
- Take what?

113
00:15:58,414 --> 00:16:01,326
- You bought everything.
- l'll take them shelves.

114
00:16:03,734 --> 00:16:07,044
So, what did you see out there
in your 15 months?

115
00:16:07,134 --> 00:16:09,523
- Such as?
- An end to all this water.

116
00:16:09,614 --> 00:16:12,970
Askin' the wrong person.

117
00:16:13,054 --> 00:16:14,965
- The one they buried today?
- Uh-huh?

118
00:16:15,054 --> 00:16:17,443
She found the only end there is.

119
00:16:22,414 --> 00:16:24,291
l've got a proposition
for you, Mariner.

120
00:16:26,094 --> 00:16:30,884
- l'm not staying.
- We're not asking you to.
All we want is your seed.

121
00:16:32,134 --> 00:16:34,932
We can look to our own
for impregnation,

122
00:16:35,014 --> 00:16:40,168
but too much of that sort of thing
gets... undesirable.

123
00:16:40,214 --> 00:16:43,092
When she's pregnant,
you go on your way...

124
00:16:43,174 --> 00:16:45,642
with all the supplies
you need.

125
00:16:45,734 --> 00:16:49,568
You don't have anything.
You're dying.

126
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:57,603
No man stays out that long
and turns down a woman.

127
00:16:58,894 --> 00:17:02,967
- He's hiding something.
- Maybe he's a Smoker spy.

128
00:17:05,454 --> 00:17:07,445
[ Whistles ]

129
00:17:12,934 --> 00:17:16,085
When the elders say so,
you can leave,

130
00:17:16,174 --> 00:17:18,005
and not before.

131
00:17:36,374 --> 00:17:38,251
Gills.

132
00:17:39,254 --> 00:17:43,133
- Mutation!
- He's a mutant!

133
00:17:43,214 --> 00:17:45,853
[ Screaming ]
My hand!

134
00:17:49,494 --> 00:17:53,043
[ Screaming ]

135
00:17:53,134 --> 00:17:56,490
[ Man Shouting,
lndistinct ]

136
00:18:00,494 --> 00:18:02,724
Throw the nets!

137
00:18:15,254 --> 00:18:19,088
[ Crowd Yelling ]

138
00:18:31,094 --> 00:18:32,971
[ Screams ]

139
00:18:33,014 --> 00:18:35,812
By what right--

140
00:18:37,174 --> 00:18:39,927
You pay me to keep the peace.

141
00:18:40,014 --> 00:18:41,845
This isn't it.

142
00:18:41,934 --> 00:18:45,210
- He has killed one of ours.
- He was defending himself.

143
00:18:45,294 --> 00:18:48,843
- He needs to be destroyed!
- Kill him. Let's kill him.
- That may be,

144
00:18:48,934 --> 00:18:52,085
but not here
and not like this.

145
00:19:22,894 --> 00:19:24,646
[ Boy ]
What is it?

146
00:19:24,734 --> 00:19:26,611
Damn.

147
00:19:27,774 --> 00:19:30,846
lt's tied.
l can't get it off.

148
00:19:34,214 --> 00:19:37,331
0pen the gate.

149
00:19:39,934 --> 00:19:42,084
[ Laughing ]

150
00:19:50,414 --> 00:19:52,450
-- [ Humming ]

151
00:20:07,334 --> 00:20:10,565
ls it a map?

152
00:20:10,614 --> 00:20:14,129
- You'd tell me if you knew,
wouldn't you, Enola?
- Mm-hmm.

153
00:20:17,454 --> 00:20:20,252
- What are you drawing?
- l don't know.

154
00:20:21,614 --> 00:20:25,892
Helen, look. Look at
the prodigal child's latest vision.

155
00:20:28,494 --> 00:20:31,292
[ Chuckling ]

156
00:20:31,374 --> 00:20:36,243
- How soon before we can leave?
- l don't have any idea yet
where we can go.

157
00:20:36,334 --> 00:20:39,531
l haven't figured out
the tattoo on her back.

158
00:20:39,574 --> 00:20:43,044
l'm a stupid man.
The answer's right there.

159
00:20:43,134 --> 00:20:45,045
lt's just beyond me.

160
00:20:47,974 --> 00:20:49,965
Maybe he knows.

161
00:20:58,294 --> 00:21:02,606
0h, yes, l see.
They are webbed.

162
00:21:02,694 --> 00:21:06,289
0ne, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight, nine,
ten digits. That's wonderful.

163
00:21:06,374 --> 00:21:09,252
They tell me, too,
that you have gills.

164
00:21:09,294 --> 00:21:13,765
lsotropic gills. Are they merely
vestigial or are they functional now?

165
00:21:13,814 --> 00:21:17,204
My name is Gregor. l've just come
to pay you a little vi-- vi--

166
00:21:18,734 --> 00:21:21,851
0h, my God.
[ Laughing ]

167
00:21:21,934 --> 00:21:24,846
l'm sorry.
l'm not laughing at you.

168
00:21:24,934 --> 00:21:27,846
l'm excited. Your gills.
They're functional.

169
00:21:27,934 --> 00:21:31,404
lcthyus sapien.
You can breathe in the water.

170
00:21:31,494 --> 00:21:35,203
How deep can you go?
Look, l'm only here...

171
00:21:35,254 --> 00:21:37,768
because l want to learn
more about you.

172
00:21:37,814 --> 00:21:39,691
[ Spitting ]

173
00:21:42,654 --> 00:21:45,885
You don't like humans
very much, do you?

174
00:21:45,934 --> 00:21:49,404
l can't say that l blame you.
But tell me:

175
00:21:49,454 --> 00:21:52,924
- Are all of your kind as
bad-tempered as you are?
- [ Slamming Cage ]

176
00:21:55,414 --> 00:21:57,769
- l have no "kind."
- 0h, fish rot.

177
00:21:57,854 --> 00:22:01,130
l'd be surprised if there
weren't others, and if there aren't,

178
00:22:01,174 --> 00:22:04,450
there will be eventually.

179
00:22:04,494 --> 00:22:07,691
Anyway, l've come here
because l need to ask you a question.

180
00:22:07,774 --> 00:22:11,528
Where-- Where did
your dirt come from?

181
00:22:11,614 --> 00:22:13,923
ls it from Dryland?

182
00:22:13,974 --> 00:22:16,010
Do you know what this is?

183
00:22:17,894 --> 00:22:20,169
The ancients-- They did something
terrible, didn't they?

184
00:22:20,254 --> 00:22:23,849
To cause all this water.
Hundreds-- Hundreds of years ago.

185
00:22:23,934 --> 00:22:26,846
lf l tell you,
will you open this lock?

186
00:22:29,254 --> 00:22:32,007
l haven't a key.

187
00:22:32,054 --> 00:22:34,693
- There's a mooring cleat down there.
- What?

188
00:22:34,734 --> 00:22:37,692
- Good as any key.
- A mooring cleat?

189
00:22:39,694 --> 00:22:42,333
l won't hurt anyone.
l'll just leave.

190
00:22:43,614 --> 00:22:46,765
- l'll be right back.
- [ Man ] Gregor!

191
00:22:46,854 --> 00:22:48,731
What's your business there?

192
00:22:48,814 --> 00:22:50,850
- Move along!
- l'm not a brave man.

193
00:22:50,894 --> 00:22:55,046
lf you know anything about Dryland,
please tell me. Please!

194
00:22:56,334 --> 00:22:58,165
Don't let it die with you.

195
00:22:58,254 --> 00:23:00,848
No, no, no, no.
Stop!

196
00:23:00,934 --> 00:23:04,449
[ Man ]
Gregor! Move along!

197
00:23:37,894 --> 00:23:42,888
[ Elder ]
After considerable deliberation
of the evidence at hand,

198
00:23:42,934 --> 00:23:46,244
it is our decision
that this mute-o...

199
00:23:46,334 --> 00:23:49,451
does, indeed,
constitute a threat.

200
00:23:49,494 --> 00:23:52,327
Therefore, in the interest
of public safety,

201
00:23:52,414 --> 00:23:55,804
he is hereby sentenced
to be recycled...

202
00:23:55,854 --> 00:23:58,607
in the customary fashion.

203
00:23:58,694 --> 00:24:00,491
Proceed.

204
00:24:06,174 --> 00:24:08,893
l'm sorry.

205
00:24:12,534 --> 00:24:14,570
Bones to berries.

206
00:24:14,614 --> 00:24:17,128
Veins to vines.

207
00:24:17,174 --> 00:24:20,803
His tendons to trees.
His blood to brine.

208
00:24:20,854 --> 00:24:23,846
Too strange for life he was.

209
00:24:23,894 --> 00:24:28,172
This mute-o now does leave us,

210
00:24:28,254 --> 00:24:30,973
recycled and entombed,

211
00:24:31,374 --> 00:24:34,127
in the presence
of Him who leads us.

212
00:24:43,694 --> 00:24:48,210
Smokers!
Dead out of the sun!

213
00:24:51,254 --> 00:24:54,564
To your posts!

214
00:25:06,734 --> 00:25:08,611
[ Confused Shouting, Screaming ]

215
00:25:08,654 --> 00:25:11,452
[ Woman ]
0h, my God! 0h, my God!

216
00:25:21,374 --> 00:25:24,013
- Kill!
- There!

217
00:25:24,054 --> 00:25:26,204
[ Screaming ]

218
00:25:30,094 --> 00:25:33,564
[ lndistinct Shouting ]

219
00:25:33,614 --> 00:25:36,333
We are safe
behind these walls.

220
00:25:37,774 --> 00:25:39,651
- Aren't we?
- [ lndistinct Shout ]

221
00:25:45,254 --> 00:25:48,212
- [ lndistinct Shout ]
- Let me out!

222
00:25:49,814 --> 00:25:52,044
Let me out!
l'll fight!

223
00:25:59,974 --> 00:26:01,805
[ Shouting Commands ]

224
00:26:20,294 --> 00:26:22,125
Give me the key
to the city now.

225
00:26:25,814 --> 00:26:28,044
Let's go!
Let's go! Let's go!

226
00:26:30,614 --> 00:26:33,412
Floor it!
Floor it! Floor it!

227
00:26:48,734 --> 00:26:51,202
[ Woman Screaming ]

228
00:26:53,774 --> 00:26:56,004
Swab it! Swab it!

229
00:26:56,094 --> 00:26:59,609
Goddamn! More ammo!

230
00:27:13,414 --> 00:27:15,370
[ Smoker ]
Break down the door!

231
00:27:15,454 --> 00:27:17,365
[ Screaming ]

232
00:27:19,014 --> 00:27:21,972
- My God!
- [ Screaming ]

233
00:27:22,054 --> 00:27:24,329
[ Woman Thrusting Spear ]
Ha!

234
00:27:24,414 --> 00:27:26,405
[ Screaming ]

235
00:27:26,454 --> 00:27:29,332
We'll have this atoll
in no time.

236
00:27:32,494 --> 00:27:34,371
Crank it!
Crank it!

237
00:27:38,254 --> 00:27:40,404
Look!

238
00:27:50,734 --> 00:27:53,328
[ Men Shouting ]

239
00:27:58,334 --> 00:28:00,450
Look out!

240
00:28:07,934 --> 00:28:10,767
[ Gunfire, Shouting ]

241
00:28:22,054 --> 00:28:23,885
0h, no!

242
00:28:34,374 --> 00:28:37,047
You get that goin'!
Fill 'em up!

243
00:28:43,494 --> 00:28:46,167
[ Smoker Yelling,
Atoll People Screaming ]

244
00:28:47,814 --> 00:28:49,770
[ Screaming ]

245
00:29:13,454 --> 00:29:16,651
- [ Gunfire ]
- [ Gregor ] Helen, come quickly!

246
00:29:16,734 --> 00:29:18,804
Helen!

247
00:29:27,774 --> 00:29:30,607
[ Man Screaming, Gunfire ]

248
00:29:45,654 --> 00:29:48,964
You're not supposed to go yet!

249
00:29:49,014 --> 00:29:51,289
lnfernal machine!

